  "body": "Im running geth in light mode.\r\n\r\nI was trying to get my tx count locally via 'pending'. This looks like it reaches into the mempool to find out if your local node has pending transactions. How come it needs to reach out to peers? I get sometimes get a 'no peer available' error on requests sometimes. Does this not work locally or does it try to get pending status from other peers as well for some type of confidence measure?",
