    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "When you create a transaction via a light client, the node doesn't know when your transaction was included, nor does it know if the transaction was dropped or not from remote nodes. It will scan incoming blocks and try to detect inclusion, but the only way to see if remote nodes still maintain it or dropped it is to ask them. It can give you a hint as to whether your transaction is underpriced or similar issues.",
